wiki.summary: With “Can’t Take a Joke,” Drake braggadociously details his busy life as a celebrity. From touching on his home life in Hidden Hills, Calabasas, to mentioning taking vacations and talking about his nightlife antics with his Reps Up Crew, Drizzy boasts about his success in the rap game while notifying his opposition that he jokingly looks down on them, as seen in the chorus of the track: I be tryna laugh with the bros ‘bout the opps that we know. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: With “Can’t Take a Joke,” Drake braggadociously details his busy life as a celebrity. From touching on his home life in Hidden Hills, Calabasas, to mentioning taking vacations and talking about his nightlife antics with his Reps Up Crew, Drizzy boasts about his success in the rap game while notifying his opposition that he jokingly looks down on them, as seen in the chorus of the track: I be tryna laugh with the bros ‘bout the opps that we know...But they can’t take a joke, 'cause it’s not one. This song is produced by up-and-coming producer ModMaxx and marks the first collaboration between him and Drake. Read more on Last.fm.
